WEBVTT

00:01.000 --> 00:02.684
<i>Previously on Z Nation...</i>

00:02.840 --> 00:05.889
WARREN: This man is the only
known survivor of a zombie bite.

00:06.040 --> 00:07.689
He's our last
best hope for humanity.

00:07.840 --> 00:09.524
What if I don't wanna be
your guinea pig?

00:09.680 --> 00:11.921
Then you'll wind up like
patient zero over there.

00:12.080 --> 00:13.809
- I’ve led them into a trap.
- Kill him.

00:15.240 --> 00:17.163
- Doc?
- You set me up, you bastard.

00:17.320 --> 00:18.845
I had no idea
this was gonna happen.

00:19.000 --> 00:20.490
- You have to believe me.
- No, I don't.

00:20.640 --> 00:22.847
I don't have to believe
anything anyone says ever again.

00:23.040 --> 00:24.485
CITIZEN Z:
A tactical nuclear weapon

00:24.640 --> 00:27.120
will be launched from NORAD
to incinerate the lab.

00:27.280 --> 00:28.850
<i>RECORDED</i> VOICE: <i>Seven minutes to detonation.</i>

00:29.000 --> 00:30.889
DOC: ls that all that's left
of Murphy?

00:31.040 --> 00:32.165
- He shed his skin.
- Holy crap.

00:32.320 --> 00:34.402
- Look.
- Let's go.

00:34.560 --> 00:36.369
God, I hate the apocalypse.

00:38.000 --> 00:44.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:45.080 --> 00:47.765
(ALARM BEEPS)

01:30.560 --> 01:33.131
(EXPLOSION)

02:53.040 --> 02:55.407
(SNARLS)

02:59.520 --> 03:01.010
(TYRES SQUEAL)

03:01.200 --> 03:03.248
Sorry!

03:40.400 --> 03:43.404
(THEME MUSIC)

03:45.520 --> 03:48.569
- SONG: ♪ Have mercy! ♪
-(THREE GUNSHOTS)

03:49.560 --> 03:55.283
♪ Oh-oh-oh-oh
Have mercy. ♪

04:36.600 --> 04:38.841
(MOANS)

04:39.920 --> 04:41.684
Ow, ow. Watch the shoulder.

04:46.720 --> 04:49.485
Holy shit.

04:49.680 --> 04:51.762
Is that snow?

04:51.920 --> 04:54.127
Nah, that's not snow.

04:54.280 --> 04:56.123
WARREN: That's ash.

04:56.280 --> 04:58.203
Radioactive fallout.

05:08.720 --> 05:12.042
(ZOMBIES MOAN)

05:24.080 --> 05:25.525
(GUNSHOT)

05:35.920 --> 05:37.684
Crap.

05:48.240 --> 05:50.720
(METAL SCRAPES)

05:53.360 --> 05:55.761
(HEAVY BREATHING)

06:08.560 --> 06:10.289
(SNARLS)

06:51.520 --> 06:55.570
(PANTS AND COUGHS)

07:21.120 --> 07:23.964
This is Citizen Z,
broadcasting on all frequencies.

07:24.120 --> 07:26.248
This is an emergency broadcast.

07:26.400 --> 07:28.687
Repeat.
This is an emergency broadcast.

07:28.880 --> 07:31.486
Literally life and death
for the human race.

07:31.640 --> 07:33.688
Now, there's a man
travelling among you.

07:33.840 --> 07:36.684
He's the only human known
to have survived a zombie bite.

07:36.840 --> 07:40.287
His blood has the antibodies
to create a vaccine.

07:40.480 --> 07:43.290
Now, it is imperative
that he be transported alive

07:43.480 --> 07:46.165
to the Centers for Disease
Control lab in California.

07:46.360 --> 07:48.328
(SNARLING)

07:50.720 --> 07:52.051
His name is Murphy.

07:52.240 --> 07:54.083
Last seen in Fort Collins,
Colorado.

07:54.280 --> 07:57.409
6'2", dark hair,
numerous bite marks on torso.

07:57.560 --> 07:59.324
Known to control zombies.

07:59.480 --> 08:00.845
Should be considered
armed and dangerous.

08:01.040 --> 08:03.168
Keep alive at all cost.

08:03.320 --> 08:06.324
Repeat.
Keep him alive at all cost.

08:10.880 --> 08:14.487
The Centers for Disease Control
is offering an enormous bounty

08:14.680 --> 08:16.011
for Murphy's safe delivery,

08:16.160 --> 08:17.924
to be paid
in whatever form you desire,

08:18.080 --> 08:21.926
as well as being first in line
for any cure developed.

08:22.080 --> 08:24.924
(RUMBLING AND CRASHING
NEARBY)

08:33.760 --> 08:35.364
If you can hear
this broadcast...

08:35.520 --> 08:39.241
Save humanity. Save yourself.

08:39.400 --> 08:41.640
Find Murphy.

09:13.080 --> 09:15.082
(SNARLING)

09:22.520 --> 09:24.682
(PANTS)

09:41.040 --> 09:42.769
They're all dead.

09:44.560 --> 09:46.289
HOW?

09:46.480 --> 09:49.609
ADDY: We were on the hill,
watching the lights.

09:49.760 --> 09:53.481
- MACK: I think those were nukes.
- ADDY: That's what I thought.

09:53.640 --> 09:55.210
ADDY: Figured
what was left of the world

09:55.400 --> 09:56.686
was trying to kill itself.

09:56.840 --> 09:59.366
Anyway, the boy they banished

09:59.520 --> 10:00.965
'cause he'd turned 13?

10:01.160 --> 10:03.970
He figured it out.
He came back.

10:04.160 --> 10:06.606
Set the whole place on fire.

10:06.760 --> 10:09.161
And released the zombie bear.

10:11.080 --> 10:13.367
Well, sounds like
she was right about men.

10:15.920 --> 10:17.490
Look, Mack...

10:30.040 --> 10:32.611
(DEEP SNARLING)

10:32.760 --> 10:34.683
Bear?

10:36.160 --> 10:37.650
Yeah.

10:44.240 --> 10:46.242
You coming or not?

10:51.480 --> 10:53.084
(STARTS ENGINE)

11:27.680 --> 11:30.286
(PEPPY MUZAK PLAYS)

11:59.760 --> 12:01.569
Come along, little doggies.

12:01.720 --> 12:04.291
I found a new set of digs
I think you're gonna like.

12:04.440 --> 12:07.171
Hey. That's a real set of Callaways
you're dragging there.

12:07.320 --> 12:08.765
- Some respect.
- MAN: Hey, friend.

12:10.880 --> 12:15.886
- Friend?
- Doing a little...shopping, huh?

12:16.040 --> 12:18.930
Presidents Day sale.

12:22.000 --> 12:24.526
These zombies of yours
are pretty tame.

12:24.720 --> 12:26.643
They're not my zombies.

12:26.800 --> 12:28.290
I would never own a...

12:29.760 --> 12:32.684
Can I help you, friend?

12:32.840 --> 12:35.320
You can start by stepping aside.

12:43.720 --> 12:45.324
What the hell
did you do that for?

12:45.480 --> 12:47.209
Your name Murphy?

12:48.200 --> 12:49.690
Nope.

12:50.920 --> 12:52.604
CITIZEN Z: His name <i>is</i> Murphy,

12:52.760 --> 12:54.364
<i>last seen in Fort Collins,
Colorado.</i>

12:54.520 --> 12:57.603
<i>6'2", dark hair,
numerous bite marks on torso.</i>

12:57.760 --> 12:59.524
<i>Known to control zombies.</i>

12:59.680 --> 13:01.409
<i>Should be considered
armed and dangerous.</i>

13:01.560 --> 13:03.449
<i>Keep alive at all cost.</i>

13:03.600 --> 13:05.250
<i>Repeat. Keep him ali...</i>

13:05.400 --> 13:08.722
Sure you're not THE Murphy?

13:10.120 --> 13:12.407
'Cause right now,
that's the only thing keeping you alive.

13:13.520 --> 13:14.806
Show me your bites.

13:14.960 --> 13:17.531
- I beg your pardon?
- You heard me.

13:17.680 --> 13:19.045
Lift up your shirt.

13:19.200 --> 13:20.645
Need to see those bites.

13:20.800 --> 13:23.121
Gotta make sure
you're the real thing.

13:28.560 --> 13:30.927
- Those are bites?
- They were.

13:31.120 --> 13:32.610
They're healing nicely,
thank you.

13:32.760 --> 13:35.969
OK, so, what if I am The Murphy,
whatever the hell that means?

13:36.120 --> 13:38.441
- So what?
-(LAUGHS) So...

13:38.600 --> 13:40.523
Everybody and their uncle's
looking for you.

13:40.680 --> 13:43.286
Government's paying a bounty
on your ass.

13:43.440 --> 13:46.649
Look, I got a whole van full of Oxy
if that's what you want.

13:46.840 --> 13:50.561
How 'bout you take half
and I'll just be on my way?

13:50.760 --> 13:54.765
How 'bout I take the Oxy and you
to California for that bounty?

13:54.920 --> 13:56.809
You're gonna take me
to California?

13:56.960 --> 14:00.442
- By yourself?
- Damn straight.

14:08.360 --> 14:10.681
Sorry. Sorry.

14:12.000 --> 14:13.161
You're insane.

14:14.680 --> 14:16.728
(YELLS)

14:17.760 --> 14:21.685
That's right. I'm insane.
And you're my prisoner.

14:22.680 --> 14:24.330
Don't worry, Mr Murphy.
I won't kill you.

14:24.480 --> 14:27.211
But I will hurt you real bad
if I need to.

14:27.360 --> 14:29.124
You understand me?
Do you...

14:29.280 --> 14:30.805
(SQUELCH!)

14:40.480 --> 14:42.164
Cassandra?

14:45.880 --> 14:48.121
Oh, I didn't know
if I'd ever see you again.

14:48.320 --> 14:50.288
(MOANS)

14:50.440 --> 14:53.762
Oh, oh! OK.
Yeah. Good to see you too.

14:53.920 --> 14:56.048
Alright. Come on.
Let's break it up here.

14:56.200 --> 14:58.680
- OK.
-(STAMMERS) Bomb...

14:58.840 --> 15:01.081
Bomb. Bomb bad. Yeah. Listen.

15:01.240 --> 15:04.050
It's not safe here.
We need to get out of here. OK?

15:04.200 --> 15:06.362
But first,
you need a makeover, girl.

15:06.520 --> 15:09.171
(COUGHS AND MOANS)

15:09.320 --> 15:11.891
No,no.No,no.
No mercy for that one.

15:12.040 --> 15:13.724
I got plans for him.

15:13.880 --> 15:15.644
Come on.

15:16.640 --> 15:18.085
Yeah, well, you should've
thought about that

15:18.240 --> 15:20.208
before you shot those innocent zombies,
shouldn't you?

15:20.360 --> 15:23.967
Let me see. Yeah.

15:24.120 --> 15:27.329
I told you that white mink
would pull it all together, didn't I?

15:28.680 --> 15:31.206
- Classy.
-(WHISPERS) Classy.

15:31.360 --> 15:33.010
Let's get out of here.

15:33.200 --> 15:35.441
Come along, Mr I'm So Badass.

15:44.600 --> 15:46.090
Let's go.

15:58.440 --> 16:01.284
-(DOC GROANS)
- WARREN: OK.

16:01.480 --> 16:03.721
-(GROANS)
- Let's get you over here.

16:06.000 --> 16:07.525
(DOC GROANS)

16:10.360 --> 16:12.010
What is it?

16:12.160 --> 16:14.049
10K: The bleeding's stopped, but...

16:14.240 --> 16:16.049
(DOC SIGHS) Just go!

16:16.240 --> 16:18.686
Find me a hole to crawl in.

16:19.920 --> 16:21.524
Leave me a weapon and some ammo.

16:21.680 --> 16:25.162
Hey. Nobody's leaving you here to die.

16:26.200 --> 16:28.771
Here. Take the last of the water.

16:30.080 --> 16:34.165
Go on.
Pretty weak myself.

16:37.440 --> 16:40.603
We wait here too long,
we might be too weak to go look for help.

16:40.760 --> 16:43.843
I've only got a day in me
without water, if that.

16:44.000 --> 16:46.241
Well, I don’t think
I'm going anywhere, Chief.

16:48.680 --> 16:50.967
10K, you stay here with Doc.

16:51.120 --> 16:53.930
I'm gonna see if I can
find food or help

16:54.080 --> 16:56.242
while I still got the strength.

16:58.360 --> 17:00.840
If I'm not back in 48 hours...

17:02.240 --> 17:04.049
...you're on your own.

17:04.200 --> 17:06.202
(SIGHS) Good luck.

17:06.359 --> 17:07.885
Thanks.

17:08.880 --> 17:11.326
(WIND WHISTLES)

17:19.800 --> 17:21.643
CITIZEN Z ON RECORDING:
<i>The Centers for Disease Control</i>

17:21.800 --> 17:23.928
<i>is offering an enormous bounty
for Murphy's safe delivery,</i>

17:24.079 --> 17:26.082
<i>to be paid in whatever form
you desire,</i>

17:26.240 --> 17:30.564
<i>as well as being first in line
for any cure developed.</i>

17:30.720 --> 17:32.643
- If you can hear <i>this...</i>
-(PUP HALF-BARKS)

17:32.800 --> 17:35.804
Shh, shh. I know, Pup.

17:35.960 --> 17:38.281
-(PUP WHIMPERS)
- I am too.

17:38.440 --> 17:40.283
(ZOMBIE GROWLS)

17:40.440 --> 17:42.169
<i>This is an emergency broadcast.</i>

17:42.320 --> 17:44.448
<i>Repeat. This is an emergency broadcast.</i>

17:44.600 --> 17:47.046
<i>Literally life and death
for the human race.</i>

17:47.200 --> 17:49.680
(EMERGENCY BROADCAST
CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY)

17:51.560 --> 17:53.210
MACK: If this works,
Warren and the others

17:53.360 --> 17:55.283
will be able to see the signal
for miles.

17:55.440 --> 17:57.090
<i>-...create a vaccine...
{STATE BUZZES)</i>

17:57.240 --> 17:58.685
- MACK: Find something?
- No.

17:58.840 --> 18:01.161
It's just that same recorded broadcast
again and again.

18:01.320 --> 18:03.721
I hope he's OK up there.

18:03.880 --> 18:08.283
WOMAN: <i>Seven, nine, eight.
Eight, three, four.</i>

18:08.480 --> 18:10.403
Just that same
weird numbers station again.

18:10.560 --> 18:12.449
You know, that's got to be
some sort of code.

18:12.600 --> 18:14.887
MACK: Wonder who needs
to keep a secret anymore.

18:15.040 --> 18:16.724
(FREQUENCIES TUNE IN AND OUT)

18:16.880 --> 18:18.882
(MAN SPEAKS INDISTINCTLY
ON RADIO)

18:34.520 --> 18:37.046
(WOMAN SPEAKS
FOREIGN LANGUAGE)

18:39.080 --> 18:40.730
-(ADDY WHISPERS) What?
- Who was that?

18:40.880 --> 18:42.882
I don't know, but they were
talking about Murphy.

18:43.040 --> 18:46.965
It was something in Spanish
and, I don't know, maybe Mandarin?

18:47.120 --> 18:50.522
ADDY: Do you think that means
he's still alive?

18:50.680 --> 18:53.126
(SIGHS) The question is...

18:54.120 --> 18:56.122
...we really still care
if he's alive?

18:57.480 --> 18:59.403
You don't care
if he's still alive,

18:59.560 --> 19:01.210
why are you trying

19:01.360 --> 19:02.930
to contact Warren
and the others, huh?

19:08.040 --> 19:09.963
Got nothing else to do, Addy.

19:50.800 --> 19:53.007
Come on, Warren.

19:54.360 --> 19:58.570
Don't die
before you can kill yourself.

20:20.280 --> 20:22.851
Three more bullets than I need.

20:26.040 --> 20:27.530
Sorry, Doc.

20:28.520 --> 20:30.568
Sorry, 10K.

20:30.720 --> 20:32.961
I tried.

20:34.760 --> 20:36.649
I tried.

20:40.800 --> 20:43.121
Lieutenant Roberta Warren...

20:44.440 --> 20:46.090
..I...

20:46.240 --> 20:48.004
...give you mercy-

20:49.880 --> 20:52.611
(GIRL SCREAMS IN DISTANCE)
Help me!

20:53.920 --> 20:56.207
Help!

20:57.880 --> 21:00.611
-(ZOMBIES GROWL)
- GIRL: Help!

21:00.760 --> 21:03.411
(ALL SNARL VICIOUSLY)

22:03.880 --> 22:05.609
(SQUELCH!)

23:04.880 --> 23:08.043
(ZOMBIE SNARLS)

23:25.080 --> 23:27.082
(GROWLS)

23:44.640 --> 23:46.005
(ZOMBIE GROWLS)

23:46.160 --> 23:48.049
Found this place
about a week ago.

23:48.200 --> 23:50.771
Looters missed the stash of
food and booze in the basement.

23:50.920 --> 23:53.321
Guess all the zombies in here
kept out the riffraff.

23:53.480 --> 23:54.925
(LAUGHS) Wait till <i>I</i> show you

23:55.120 --> 23:56.804
what I've been teaching
the locals.

23:56.960 --> 23:59.531
Cassandra?
Hey, where'd you go?

24:05.120 --> 24:06.929
Do you like
what I picked out for you?

24:07.080 --> 24:09.082
(WHISPERS) Yes.

24:13.200 --> 24:15.680
(ZOMBIE SNARLS)

24:20.160 --> 24:22.242
(LAUGHS)

24:22.400 --> 24:24.448
Don't be afraid.
He won't bite.

24:24.600 --> 24:26.841
And even if he did,
you're immune, remember?

24:27.000 --> 24:33.246
(SLOWLY) I'm not a zombie.

24:33.400 --> 24:35.084
I know.

24:35.280 --> 24:37.203
You're better.

24:39.120 --> 24:41.088
I've been working on
my zombie whispering.

24:41.240 --> 24:43.720
Come on.
Let me show you.

24:45.120 --> 24:47.600
This is Telulah and Gigi.

24:47.760 --> 24:50.127
Check this out.

24:52.160 --> 24:55.721
Ladies. Let's show her
what we've been working on.

25:13.240 --> 25:15.481
-(TELULAH AND GIGI GROWL)
- MURPHY: Oh, come on.

25:15.640 --> 25:19.042
Come on, ladies!
That's not right.

25:19.240 --> 25:22.289
Ladies! Ladies, please!

25:22.440 --> 25:24.488
We talked about this.

25:38.200 --> 25:40.202
(GROANS SOFTLY)

25:53.880 --> 25:55.882
(KETTLE WHISTLES)

25:59.920 --> 26:01.365
(CLATTERING)

26:01.520 --> 26:04.490
She's awake.
The lady's awake.

26:06.600 --> 26:10.321
Mama, Papa,
I want you to meet my hero.

26:11.680 --> 26:13.409
Please, sit down and eat.

26:13.560 --> 26:16.086
WOMAN: You must be starving.

26:19.240 --> 26:21.004
Thank you.

26:28.600 --> 26:31.729
WOMAN <i>ON</i> RADIO: <i>Five. Five, three, seven.</i>

26:31.880 --> 26:33.962
<i>Seven, nine, eight.</i>

26:34.120 --> 26:36.726
<i>Eight, three, four.</i>

26:36.880 --> 26:40.521
<i>Five, one, three. Seven.</i>

26:47.000 --> 26:48.684
Maybe it's just some...

26:48.840 --> 26:51.241
...giant cosmic bingo game
somewhere, huh?

26:51.400 --> 26:52.925
It's probably all just
canned civil defence broadcasts

26:53.080 --> 26:54.411
triggered by the nukes.

26:54.560 --> 26:56.005
Well.

26:56.160 --> 26:58.322
(ADDY WHISPERS) <i>I</i> just...

26:58.480 --> 27:01.211
...l just wish
we'd hear from somebody.

27:02.840 --> 27:04.490
Anybody at all...

27:06.000 --> 27:07.650
...who's alive.

27:07.800 --> 27:10.326
(GROANING, THUD)

27:31.240 --> 27:33.720
-(ZOMBIE SNARLS)
- ADDY: Mack!

27:33.920 --> 27:36.321
- Mack!
-(GROWLS)

27:37.320 --> 27:39.049
Mack! Mack, watch his teeth!

27:39.200 --> 27:41.009
I'm trying! Hit him!

27:41.160 --> 27:43.367
- I can't get a clear shot!
- Hit him, please!

27:44.400 --> 27:47.290
MACK: Come on! (GRUNTS)

27:47.440 --> 27:49.204
(GUNSHOT)

27:53.680 --> 27:55.489
10K: 3,099!

27:56.680 --> 27:58.967
DOC: We saw your signal!

28:02.000 --> 28:04.401
WARREN: You've made a real life
for yourselves here.

28:04.560 --> 28:06.210
WOMAN:
Have some more goat cheese.

28:06.360 --> 28:08.249
My husband's been monitoring the milk
for fallout,

28:08.400 --> 28:10.243
but so far,
the winds have spared us.

28:10.400 --> 28:13.244
No, thank you -
I've eaten so much already.

28:13.400 --> 28:15.368
My body doesn't know
what the hell is going on.

28:15.520 --> 28:17.522
I haven't had real food
for weeks.

28:17.680 --> 28:19.523
Gave myself up for dead.

28:19.680 --> 28:21.444
We've all been there.

28:25.040 --> 28:26.724
(LAUGHS)

28:27.920 --> 28:29.445
We don't get many visitors.

28:29.640 --> 28:31.642
Oh. How 'bout you?
How you doing?

28:31.800 --> 28:33.450
- A lot better.
- WARREN: Yeah.

28:33.600 --> 28:36.843
Now she knows why we don't
go digging for roots alone.

28:37.000 --> 28:38.764
There were never zombies there
before.

28:38.920 --> 28:40.410
MAN: It's the damn nukes.

28:40.560 --> 28:43.040
Everything's screwed up now,
even the weather.

28:43.240 --> 28:46.323
Yeah. Well...

28:46.480 --> 28:48.164
I have two partners
that are still out there,

28:48.320 --> 28:49.810
and I should be
getting back to them.

28:49.960 --> 28:53.567
Alright, then.
I'm gonna pack you some provisions.

28:53.720 --> 28:54.767
Thanks.

28:55.840 --> 28:57.410
Come here.

29:02.160 --> 29:03.810
Alright - from what I've heard,

29:03.960 --> 29:06.247
everything west
of this line here

29:06.400 --> 29:08.084
is a no-go zone.

29:08.240 --> 29:11.767
And there's more fallout here
and over here.

29:11.920 --> 29:14.207
And I think that's
the tunnel where we crashed,

29:14.360 --> 29:16.488
so that would put my friends
somewhere in there.

29:16.640 --> 29:18.404
Yeah, that's about
a 2-day hike.

29:18.560 --> 29:20.528
A little less
if you go over the mountain.

29:20.680 --> 29:22.444
Got it.

29:22.600 --> 29:25.206
GIRL: "..and so,
seizing the larger by the ears,

29:25.360 --> 29:28.443
"he jumped on his back
and, to my great amusement,

29:28.600 --> 29:32.207
"coolly rode to meet me
as I came up the hatchway."

29:34.200 --> 29:35.645
Do you have to go?

29:35.800 --> 29:38.371
Yeah, sweetie.
I have to go.

29:38.520 --> 29:40.488
I have a job to do.

29:40.640 --> 29:42.608
Come back and tell us
how it turns out.

29:42.800 --> 29:44.643
Promise?

29:46.280 --> 29:48.169
Promise.

29:51.960 --> 29:53.564
Good luck
with that Murphy fella.

29:53.720 --> 29:55.563
Yeah.

30:01.400 --> 30:03.641
My husband told me
what you did out there.

30:03.800 --> 30:05.802
It must have been horrible.

30:07.040 --> 30:09.008
I don't know how to thank you.

30:10.640 --> 30:13.883
Those kids -
those beautiful kids.

30:14.080 --> 30:16.606
That's how you'll thank me.

30:16.760 --> 30:20.651
I was ready to die,
and I needed a reason to live.

30:20.800 --> 30:23.531
Those kids...

30:23.680 --> 30:25.364
...they're that reason.

30:25.520 --> 30:27.010
Thank you.

30:30.320 --> 30:31.890
Good luck.

30:32.040 --> 30:33.565
WARREN: Got it.

31:17.240 --> 31:19.242
(VEHICLE APPROACHES)

31:58.200 --> 32:00.328
Oh, hey,
my Spanish is terrible,

32:00.520 --> 32:02.329
but I'm sure this is
what they were talking about.

32:02.520 --> 32:04.522
I wonder who else
heard that broadcast.

32:04.680 --> 32:06.364
10 o'clock!

32:06.520 --> 32:09.444
I see them.
Just keep going!

32:15.720 --> 32:18.371
Folks are friendly
here in Cheyenne.

32:18.520 --> 32:20.329
Friendly ain't the vibe
I'm getting.

32:20.480 --> 32:22.642
Let's find Murphy
and get the hell out of Dodge.

32:22.800 --> 32:25.565
- Cheyenne.
- Whatever.

32:27.360 --> 32:29.601
OK, so we all need
to think like Murphy.

32:29.800 --> 32:31.609
Get inside his zombified head.

32:31.800 --> 32:33.723
And I know
that's a scary place to be.

32:33.880 --> 32:36.451
But where would you hide
if you were Murphy?

32:42.280 --> 32:44.521
Hey, hold on!

32:45.520 --> 32:47.727
You say think like Murphy?

32:47.880 --> 32:50.042
Hell, they might as well
have his picture on the sign.

32:55.880 --> 32:57.882
(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)

32:59.720 --> 33:02.007
(ZOMBIES SNARL QUIETLY)

33:05.080 --> 33:06.809
(ZOMBIES WHEEZE)

33:07.800 --> 33:09.450
He)'. guys.

33:11.040 --> 33:12.849
-(DOOR CREAKS SHUT)
- Ahhh.

33:13.000 --> 33:14.843
What the hell
took you so long?

33:15.000 --> 33:17.731
Murphy, you sonofabitch.

33:17.880 --> 33:19.962
Yeah. What she said.

33:20.120 --> 33:21.963
Now, now, Roberta.

33:22.120 --> 33:24.327
Is that any way to talk
to an old friend?

33:24.520 --> 33:27.171
-(BOTTLES SMASH)
-(ZOMBIES SNARL)

33:27.320 --> 33:29.049
Hey,hey,hey,hey,
hey,hey.hey-

33:31.520 --> 33:33.363
That hurt.

33:33.520 --> 33:36.444
Oh. I'm just getting started.

33:36.600 --> 33:38.523
Now, come on, Chief. Hey.

33:38.680 --> 33:40.523
Don't forget the mission.

33:40.680 --> 33:43.286
Come on.

33:48.200 --> 33:50.043
You damn near got us killed.

33:50.200 --> 33:52.487
And you did kill
millions of other people.

33:52.640 --> 33:54.927
Didn't you get the memo?

33:55.080 --> 33:58.368
The apocalypse means never
having to say you're sorry.

33:58.520 --> 34:00.522
I was just following
the prime directive

34:00.720 --> 34:03.963
of this mission -
save Murphy's ass.

34:04.120 --> 34:05.884
Let's not forget -

34:06.040 --> 34:08.646
if I die, party's over
for the human race.

34:08.800 --> 34:11.246
If you want
to blame somebody,

34:11.440 --> 34:13.362
blame that nutjob Dr Kurian.

34:13.520 --> 34:15.761
Or your little buddy
Citizen Z.

34:15.920 --> 34:17.888
Maybe we should tie you up
for your own good.

34:18.040 --> 34:20.520
-(CASSANDRA HISSES)
- Cassandra.

34:22.239 --> 34:24.242
10K: You're alive.

34:27.600 --> 34:29.601
Cassandra?

34:32.080 --> 34:33.889
- What did you do to her?
- MURPHY: Saved her life.

34:34.040 --> 34:35.929
- What did you do?
-(HISSES)

34:38.560 --> 34:40.369
I'm sorry.
What is she wearing?

34:40.520 --> 34:43.205
Is that mildly impractical
for the apocalypse?

34:43.360 --> 34:45.806
You try dressing a classy lady
in Cheyenne, Wyoming.

34:45.960 --> 34:47.803
Hey, is anybody else concerned

34:47.960 --> 34:50.088
that there's all these Zs
standing around here?

34:50.239 --> 34:52.083
MURPHY: Hey, don't worry.
They're friendly.

34:52.239 --> 34:54.322
As long as I'm friendly.

34:54.480 --> 34:56.447
Come on, Murphy.

34:56.600 --> 34:58.728
We got to get you
to California.

34:58.880 --> 35:01.929
Yeah.
Um, about California...

35:02.120 --> 35:03.929
You know,
after everything that happened,

35:04.120 --> 35:05.884
the nukes and all,

35:06.080 --> 35:07.889
I'm not so sure I'm down

35:08.080 --> 35:09.889
with the whole
saving humanity thing.

35:10.080 --> 35:12.731
I'm not so sure
humanity's worth saving.

35:12.920 --> 35:15.161
You're going to California.

35:15.320 --> 35:17.084
You don't even know
if California's still there.

35:17.240 --> 35:20.164
If you won't do it for humanity,
do it for yourself, Murphy.

35:20.320 --> 35:22.004
You need that vaccine
more than anybody.

35:22.160 --> 35:23.969
Have you looked
in the mirror lately?

35:24.120 --> 35:26.122
You may be styling,
but you're turning zombie, brother.

35:26.280 --> 35:29.090
Brother, maybe there are worse
things than being a zombie.

35:30.400 --> 35:32.801
Maybe being
a starving, fearful,

35:32.960 --> 35:34.962
violent, vindictive human

35:35.120 --> 35:37.168
is worse.

35:38.880 --> 35:41.690
But, hey, it is the apocalypse!

35:41.840 --> 35:44.730
Let's have some fun!
Let me show you what I've been working on.

35:44.880 --> 35:47.770
Come on. Grab a seat.
You're gonna love this.

35:49.760 --> 35:52.366
The apocalypse will still be
waiting for us when we're done.

35:52.520 --> 35:54.170
Cassandra!

35:55.160 --> 35:57.003
-(ENGINE STARTS)
- Hey, hey, hey, hey!

35:57.160 --> 35:59.686
Ah, so nice to see
so many familiar faces

35:59.880 --> 36:01.723
in the audience tonight!

36:01.880 --> 36:03.723
Ladies and gentlemen,

36:03.880 --> 36:05.644
let's hear it for the one,

36:05.800 --> 36:07.450
the only...

36:07.640 --> 36:09.369
...Chantrelle.

36:11.800 --> 36:14.883
(SLOW MOODY MUSIC PLAYS)

36:18.840 --> 36:20.842
(GRUNTING)

36:26.520 --> 36:29.171
Oh...my...God.

36:30.160 --> 36:32.367
DOC: Well, I hope
she ain't working for tips.

36:38.120 --> 36:39.963
(GRUNTS)

36:40.120 --> 36:41.963
Whoa!

36:42.120 --> 36:44.122
I'm having a deja vu.

36:45.800 --> 36:47.404
- Murphy.
- I know, right?

36:47.600 --> 36:49.204
Wait. lt gets better.

36:52.880 --> 36:55.201
(SNARLS QUIETLY)

37:00.760 --> 37:02.649
(SNARLS FASTER)

37:10.920 --> 37:12.410
(CRASH!)

37:12.560 --> 37:14.130
(MUSIC STOPS)

37:14.280 --> 37:15.805
Ta-da!

37:16.000 --> 37:18.048
I know. I know.
The finale needs a little work.

37:18.200 --> 37:21.841
But, hey, let's hear it
for Chantrelle!

37:22.000 --> 37:25.721
(LAUGHS) Oh, come on!

37:25.880 --> 37:27.564
(ONE PERSON CLAPS SLOWLY)

37:30.240 --> 37:32.686
ls this a private show
or can anybody watch?

37:33.920 --> 37:36.890
Ah, ah, ah. Leave your weapons
right where they are.

37:37.040 --> 37:39.008
Don't make me
have to shoot anybody.

37:39.160 --> 37:41.003
There's enough zombies
in this world already.

37:41.160 --> 37:42.650
What do you want?

37:42.800 --> 37:44.802
Your name wouldn't happen
to be Murphy, would it?

37:48.600 --> 37:50.648
Nope.

37:54.480 --> 37:57.051
- Lot of people looking for you, Mr Murphy.
- That so?

37:57.200 --> 37:59.487
This man, he's our prisoner.

37:59.640 --> 38:01.290
Well, he's my prisoner now.

38:01.440 --> 38:03.727
Uh, no, sorry. She's right.
We got dibs on him.

38:03.920 --> 38:05.922
Yeah. And we're taking him
to California.

38:06.080 --> 38:08.447
No, you're not.
He's coming with me.

38:08.600 --> 38:10.728
- Where?
- To the highest bidder.

38:10.880 --> 38:12.723
CDC in California
aren't the only ones

38:12.880 --> 38:14.689
willing to pay for his blood.

38:14.840 --> 38:16.842
Why does everybody
always talk about me

38:17.000 --> 38:19.002
like I am not
standing right here?

38:19.160 --> 38:21.003
You know,
there's only one problem

38:21.160 --> 38:23.401
with all of your plans
for The Murphy.

38:24.880 --> 38:26.882
I ain't going anywhere
with any of you.

38:27.040 --> 38:30.169
- Hit it!
-(MOODY MUSIC RESUMES)

38:30.320 --> 38:33.608
(ZOMBIES GROWL)

38:35.200 --> 38:37.362
(GUNSHOTS)

38:37.520 --> 38:39.010
(GROWLS)

38:39.160 --> 38:40.650
- Argh!
-(GUNSHOT)

38:40.800 --> 38:43.406
(ZOMBIES GROWL)

38:44.840 --> 38:46.126
(TWO GUNSHOTS)

38:46.280 --> 38:48.009
(GROWLS)

39:01.800 --> 39:03.564
(ZOMBIE SNARLS)

39:12.360 --> 39:14.124
(ZOMBIE GROWLS)

39:14.280 --> 39:16.328
(BOTTLE SMASHES)

39:36.760 --> 39:38.603
- We gotta get out of here.
- I know.

39:38.760 --> 39:40.603
- I can't stand this music.
- Let's go!

39:40.760 --> 39:42.762
(ZOMBIES SNARL)

39:55.240 --> 39:56.685
(SNARLS)

40:02.800 --> 40:05.087
(ZOMBIE SNARLS)

40:07.200 --> 40:09.771
(ZOMBIE GRUNTS)

40:10.760 --> 40:13.411
- Warren!
-(MACK SHOUTS)

40:13.560 --> 40:15.403
-(ZOMBIE GROWLS)
-(WARREN GROANS)

40:17.400 --> 40:19.971
- Look out!
-(ZOMBIE SNARLS)

40:20.120 --> 40:21.849
Argh!

40:22.000 --> 40:23.968
(GRUNTS)

40:24.120 --> 40:26.361
(GROANS)

40:47.280 --> 40:50.250
What do we do now, Chief?

40:50.400 --> 40:52.846
WARREN: I made a promise
to a little girl

40:53.000 --> 40:54.968
and I'm gonna keep it.

40:55.120 --> 40:57.009
We are going to find Murphy,

40:57.160 --> 40:59.288
get him to California,

40:59.440 --> 41:02.683
and they're going to make a vaccine
and save the world.

41:02.840 --> 41:04.683
And I'm gonna kill
any bounty hunter

41:04.840 --> 41:06.205
that gets in my way.

41:06.400 --> 41:07.925
Sounds like a plan.

41:09.160 --> 41:12.403
- Any idea which way Murphy went?
-(TYRES SCREECH)

41:14.480 --> 41:16.005
He went that-a-way.

41:21.200 --> 41:23.328
(ELECTRONIC BLEEPING)

41:23.480 --> 41:25.721
(PUP WHINES AND PANTS)

41:25.920 --> 41:27.490
OK.

41:27.640 --> 41:29.881
No matter what happens,
you stay.

41:30.880 --> 41:33.565
Yeah, that's a good boy.

41:47.720 --> 41:50.963
Remember, no matter
what you hear, you stay.

42:24.520 --> 42:26.124
OK, sweetie.

42:27.120 --> 42:29.122
Which way is Daddy?

42:36.680 --> 42:38.682
(SQUEAKY NOISES
FROM STOMACH)

42:42.600 --> 42:44.921
Left it is.

